        <div><a name="care"></a>
            <div class="detailed">
                <h2>Lawn Care Services<a href="#top">Back to Top</a></h2>

                <h4>Renovation Services</h4>
                <p><span>Single Core Aeration/Double Core Aeration</span> &mdash; Essential service for the long-term health of your lawn.  Aeration loosens hard compacted clay soil and allows increased oxygen flow to your lawns root system.  It also will improve water absorption and prevent run-off.  Also aids in seed  germination when performed with Over-Seeding service.</p>
                <p><span>Over-Seeding</span> &mdash; We apply premium quality grass seed with the highest germination rates available.  Over-seeding will help repair stressed areas and improves your lawn's overall ability to resist disease.  Over-seeding will help replace the grass that was damaged or destroyed during the growing season.</p>

                <h4>Additional Lawn Care Services</h4>
                <p><span>Grub Control</span> &mdash; Grubs are prevalent in our area and the damage they do to your lawns root system can be devastating.  This is usually coordinated with our fertilization program but can be a stand alone treatment.</p>
                <p><span>Disease Control</span> &mdash; We can apply fungicide as a preventative measure or to treat a break-out of several types of fungus including Summer’s Patch, Dollar Spots, and Brown Patch</p>

                <h4>Tree/Shrub Care Program</h4>
                <p><span>Spring/Fall Dormant Oil</span> &mdash; Oil Spray smothers eggs of aphids, scales, mites, and other pests.</p>
                <p><span>Insect/Disease Control</span> &mdash; Spray an insecticide which prevents insects and disease from harming your trees/shrubs.</p>
                <p><span>Fall Deep Root Fertilization</span> &mdash; Fertilizer injected deep into root system of your trees/shrubs.</p>
                <p><span>Ornamental Tree Pruning</span> &mdash; Trimming off new growth after plants have bloomed will help maintain the appropriate size and appearance of your ornamental trees and shrubs.</p>

                <h4>Ornamental Bed Maintenance</h4>
                <p><span>Mulch Installation</span> &mdash; High grade double ground hardwood bark mulch.  $70 per cubic yard, please call for quote.</p>
                <p><span>Pre-Emergent Bed Weed Control</span> &mdash; Applied to beds in early spring to prevent weed growth.  Usually applied with mulch installation</p>
                <p><span>Fall Deep Root Fertilization</span> &mdash; Fertilizer injected deep into root system of your trees/shrubs.</p>
                <p><span>Ornamental Tree Pruning</span> &mdash; Trimming off new growth after plants have bloomed will help maintain the appropriate size and appearance of your ornamental trees and shrubs.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
